An: Haha. I thought he was fine after spending yesterday teaching him, but I guess it just isn't that easy. Maybe we should go help them.
An: Kohane! Toya!
Kohane: Hi, An! How'd your contest go?
An: Everything's back to being even after me winning just now! But I'm definitely gonna win it all in the end!
Toya: I see... I wish I could do what you and Akito can do, Shiraishi. I still have quite a bit of work ahead of me it seems.
An: You just need some time to get the hang of it, Toya! I mean, I've been coming here since I was really little.
Akito: Yeah, same here. Still, I wasn't expecting to go on a New Year's skiing trip together...
Toya: We have Ken and his friends to thank for that.
An: Yeah! I couldn't believe it when my dad and his friend asked us to do a show at their lodge... But thanks to them we get to be here! Lucky us!
Kohane: Hehe. That's true.
Kohane: It's so nice to spend New Year's together like this.
???: “What a wonderfully snowy village!”
Toya: Hm? That voice... But there's no reason for him to be...
Akito: No... Based on my experience, he appears when you least expect it...
Snake Deity: “Brr... So cold! I will need to go into brumation to survive this.”
Lion-Dog: “But it's so pretty! There's snow as far as the eye can see! I really wanna run around in it!”
Tsukasanosuke: “Yes, I can empathize. You do not come across such beauty every day. I, Tsukasanosuke Tenma, feel very moved by this view!”
Akito: I knew it...
Kohane: Oh, does this mean Wonderlands×Showtime is going to do a show...?! Here of all places...?!
Miku: <We wouldn't want them to see us, so we should probably hide.>
MEIKO: <Yes, I agree.>
Shapeshifting Fox: “Well, it is nice to see a troupe like this for a change. It may actually be worth this shapeshifting fox's time to join in on the festivities.”
Shapeshifting Fox: “Let us see how it goes... Hello there, traveling performer. Do you have a moment?”
Tsukasanosuke: “Hm? Yes, what is it? Ah, could it be that you wish to perform with us?!”
Shapeshifting Fox: “Yes, more or less. I happen to be well versed in these sorts of performances, so I believe my skills will be of some service to you.”
Tsukasanosuke: “Really?! Then, we would love to have you!”
Shapeshifting Fox: “However, I do not wish to take part in any poorly thought-out performances. I must see more before I deem your show worthy...”
Shapeshifting Fox: “So, do not mind me. Please perform as you all normally do.”
Snake Deity: “Perform? For you...?”
Tsukasanosuke: “For someone who wishes to join us on our journey, you ask quite a lot of us...”
Tsukasanosuke: “However, I also find that admirable! So, in that case...!”
Tsukasanosuke: “You are more than welcome to join us!!!”
Shapeshifting Fox: “Hmm...”
Tsukasanosuke: “H-Hm? You seem dissatisfied...!”
Snake Deity: “Of course he is... I strongly doubt that he is some sort of simpleton.”
Lion-Dog: “So, what do we do?”
Lion-Dog: “Oh, I know! Let's have everyone here help us!”
Tsukasanosuke: “Ah, excellent idea! These villagers can... Hm?!”
Kohane: Huh? Is Tsukasa looking towards us...?
Akito: Toya, don't make eye contact...
Toya: I have a feeling that he has already seen us...
Tsukasanosuke: “You there, villagers! Let us hear what you think!”
Akito: Ugh, really...?
Tsukasanosuke: “I would very much like to have that fox join us, but he will not at this rate.”
Tsukasanosuke: “Do you know of any better ways to invite someone to join your troupe?”
Kohane: H-how to invite someone...? U-Uhh...
Toya: That's actually a very difficult question.
An: Invite them... To join your troupe...
An: What if you made him excited somehow? You could try convincing him that great things will happen if he joins you!
Snake Deity: “Excited, huh...? Yes, that is an interesting proposition!”
Lion-Dog: “Oh, then! Can you tell us what makes you excited the most?”
An: Me? Well... Whenever I hear a song like this!
Tsukasanosuke: “Hm?”
